            <h5>REROLLING</h5>
            <p>
                Moving people on to a new class is something we might utilize as a tool to strenghten the roster. And it's important for us to share the guidelines for this process.
            </p>
            <p>
                We categorize rerolls in to two group.
            </p>
            <p>
                <li>We reach out to a player of a certain class, and ask them if they are interested in moving over to an alt - this will typically be done to improve our roster.</li>
                <li>You as a player contact our recruitment officer, and get approved to reroll through the guild leadership.</li>
            </p>
            <p>
                At no point is this decision up to the individual player alone, but something that needs to be approved on a guild leadership level.
                People who do end up being approved for a reroll will hold full responsibility for their performance, and will be treated as any other main in the guild.
            </p>
            <p>
                <center><b>Think it through as you wont be able to reverse this descision - if you decide to reroll.</b></center>
            </p>
